      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "OLYMPIA, Feb. 17.-Work may\nbe stopped on the state buildings\nat the A. Y. P. exposition, accord\ning to Representative Slayden, one\nof the state commission. Slayden\nsays the commissioners agreed to\npay cash for the work because the\ncontractors refused to accept the\nwarrants.\n\n\nA new A. Y. P. bill passed this\nsession at the request of Slayden\nand others of the commission was\namended to require that all the\nexpenditures should be made on\nvouchers similarly to the expendi-\nlures of other state institutions.\n\n\nThis was to prevent what has\nbeen a scandal in many commits\nsion matters in the history of this\nand other states. When the COM\nmissions are free to spend the coin"
